>Description:
I'm filing this as a feature request since it's not really a bug,
but a UI/convenience issue.

I installed a Minimal Racket on Windows and then installed
DrRacket through the package system. The DrRacket executable was
successfully built, but it's put in a pretty obscure place:
  C:\\User\\asumu\\AppData\\Roaming\\Racket\\snapshot\\DrRacket.exe

Most users probably won't install a minimal build, so maybe this
isn't a big deal, but it doesn't seem like a great default. Would
it be possible to put them in the Racket install folder if it's
writable?
>How-To-Repeat:

>Fix:
>Audit-Trail:
From: Sam Tobin-Hochstadt <samth@cs.indiana.edu>
